text: The risk of transmitting Covid-19 from an unmasked person to an unmasked person is 90%. From an unmasked person to a masked person it is 30%. From a masked person to an unmasked person it is 5%. From a masked person to a masked person it is 1.5%.
Graphics show the exact probability of COVID-19 carriers spreading the disease if they or another person wears a mask
85% of people who test positive for Covid wore masks always or often.
Stanford study found masks are ineffective to block transmission of Covid-19
There’s a ‘positive correlation’ between higher mask usage and COVID-19 deaths.
